      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Right on with Balducci's. I have been going there since the late 50's when I was a student at New York University and their first place was on Greenwich Avenue. The old man tallied up your purchases with a crayon on a brown bag.</p>
        <p>I happened into the new spot and found it wanting on all levels. There was not a knowledgeable person on the entire staff -- all kids who knew not a sourdough from osso bucco. It took 25 minutes to get a half pound of Irish salmon, and it was very poorly cut to boot. Sad. The West Side has too many good shops and too savvy a clientele to support this operation.</p>
        <p>ROBERT W. MARTIN  New York</p>
      </block>
